Miss Universe Japan 2017
Date July 4, 2017
Venue Hotel Chinzanso Tokyo, Bunkyō, Tokyo, Japan
Entrants 47
Placements 16
Winner Momoko Abe
 Chiba

Miss Universe Japan 2017 (Japanese: 2017 ミス・ユニバース・ジャパン), the Miss Universe Japan pageant, will take place in the Hotel Chinzanso Tokyo, Bunkyō, Tokyo, Japan, on July 4, 2017.[1] Sari Nakazawa from Shiga will crown her successor at the end of the event. The winner will represent Japan in Miss Universe 2017.[2]
